{"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.16","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigrationGuides"]]},"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"ComposableArchitecture"}],"roleHeading":"Article","title":"Migrating to 1.16","role":"article"},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"There are no steps needed to migrate to 1.16 of the Composable Architecture, but there has been","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a change to the underlying behavior of ","type":"text"},{"code":".appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" that one should be aware of. When using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"code":".appStorage","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" with ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", if your key does not contain the characters “.” or “@”, then changes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"to that key in "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UserDefaults"},{"type":"text","text":" will be observed using key-value observing (KVO)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Otherwise, "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NotificationCenter"},{"type":"text","text":" will be used to observe changes."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"KVO is a far more efficient way of observing changes to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"UserDefaults"},{"type":"text","text":" and it works cross-process,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"such as from widgets and app extensions. However, KVO does not work when the keys contain “.”"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"or “@”, and so in those cases we must use the cruder tool of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NotificationCenter"},{"type":"text","text":". That is not"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"as efficient, and it forces us to perform a thread-hop when the notification is posted before"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"we can update the ","type":"text"},{"code":"@Shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" value. For this reason it is not possible to animate changes that are","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"made directly to ","type":"text"},{"code":"UserDefaults","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":":","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["withAnimation {","  \/\/ ⚠️ This will not animate any SwiftUI views using '@Shared(.appStorage(\"co.pointfree.count\"))'","  UserDefaults.standard.set(0, forKey: \"co.pointfree.count\")","}"]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"In general, we recommend using other delimeters for your keys, such as “\/”, “:”, “-”, etc.:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift","code":["@Shared(.appStorage(\"co:pointfree:count\")) var count = 0"]}]}],"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".appStorage"},{"type":"text","text":" strategy used with "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"@Shared"},{"type":"text","text":" now uses key-value observing instead of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"NotificationCenter"},{"type":"text","text":" when possible. Learn how this may affect your code."}],"kind":"article","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/composablearchitecture\/migratingto1.16"]}],"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"minor":3,"major":0,"patch":0},"seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.19","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.18","doc:\/\/ComposableArchitecture\/documentation\/ComposableArchitecture\/MigratingTo1.17.1","doc: